        "file_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/plans/eager-booping-goblet.md",
        "content": "# Snake and Ladder Game - Implementation Plan\n\n## Context\nBuild a classic Snake and Ladder board game as a single self-contained HTML file. Two players take turns rolling a dice and moving across a 10x10 board (squares 1-100). Landing on a snake sends the player down; landing on a ladder moves them up. First to reach square 100 wins.\n\n## Technology\n- Single HTML file with embedded CSS and JavaScript\n- Canvas-based board rendering\n- No external dependencies\n\n## File to Create\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/snake-and-ladder.html`\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Board Layout\n- 10x10 grid (100 squares), numbered 1-100 in snake pattern (bottom-left to top-right, alternating direction per row)\n- Each cell shows its number\n- Color-coded snakes (red) and ladders (green) drawn on the board\n\n### Snakes and Ladders Configuration\nStandard positions:\n- **Ladders**: 2->38, 7->14, 8->31, 15->26, 21->42, 28->84, 36->44, 51->67, 71->91, 78->98\n- **Snakes**: 16->6, 46->25, 49->11, 62->19, 64->60, 74->53, 89->68, 92->88, 95->75, 99->80\n\n### Game Mechanics\n1. Two players (Player 1 = blue, Player 2 = red)\n2. Click \"Roll Dice\" button to roll (random 1-6)\n3. Player token moves to new position\n4. If landing on snake head -> slide down to tail\n5. If landing on ladder bottom -> climb to top\n6. Must land exactly on 100 to win (if roll overshoots, stay in place)\n7. Display current turn, dice result, and game status\n\n### UI Structure\n- **Header**: Game title and current player indicator\n- **Board**: Canvas element rendering the 10x10 grid with snakes/ladders\n- **Controls**: Roll Dice button, dice result display, status messages\n- **Footer**: New Game / Reset button\n\n### Rendering Approach\n- Use HTML5 Canvas for the board\n- Draw grid lines and numbers\n- Draw snakes as curved red lines with head markers\n- Draw ladders as parallel green lines with rungs\n- Player tokens as colored circles on their current square\n\n## Verification\n1. Open `snake-and-ladder.html` in a browser\n2. Verify board renders with all 100 numbered squares\n3. Click Roll Dice - verify dice shows 1-6 and player moves\n4. Verify snakes slide player down and ladders move player up\n5. Verify turn alternates between players\n6. Verify win condition at square 100\n7. Verify Reset/New Game works\n"
    },
    "tool_use_id": "toolu_014cWMNCsG4EV1WhwQLSioZ1"
}
