        "content": "# Plan: Workflow Auditor Assessment\n\n## Context\n\nAfter implementing new deliverables features (`filepath`, placeholders, exact match), we need to verify if the workflow auditor needs updates.\n\n---\n\n## Analysis\n\n**Data Flow:**\n1. `unified_loader.py` - Resolves `{project}`/`{session}` placeholders \u2192 stores as `regex_pattern`\n2. `deliverables_tracker.py` - Stores `regex_pattern` as `pattern` in state.json\n3. `workflow_auditor.py` - Reads `pattern` field for violation messages\n\n**Key Code:**\n- Auditor line 110: `pattern = d.get(\"pattern\", d.get(\"value\", \"?\"))`\n- Tracker line 43: `\"pattern\": item.regex_pattern or item.pattern`\n- Loader line 452: `resolved_filepath = resolve_filepath_placeholders(filepath)`\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\n**No code changes needed to `workflow_auditor.py`.**\n\nThe auditor already correctly:\n- Reads `pattern` field which contains resolved paths\n- Shows resolved patterns in violation messages (correct behavior)\n- Handles `strict_order` violations with proper context\n\nThe new features (`filepath`, placeholders, `./` prefix) are transparent to the auditor because they're processed before deliverables reach state.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\nRun existing tests to confirm no regressions:\n```bash\npython -m pytest .claude/hooks/workflow/tests/test_workflow_auditor.py -v\n```\n"
    },
